      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Ferdinand Mosca</b>\n</p><p><b>Ferdinand Mosca</b>,<br />\na Filipino mechanical engineer - mainly as piping engineer/designer on oil and gas projects, software developer and chess programmer. He is author of the chess engines <a href=\"/Deuterium\" title=\"Deuterium\">Deuterium</a> and <a href=\"/index.php?title=CDrill&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"CDrill (page does not exist)\">CDrill</a>, the latter with the aim to play like human at a rating below 2000 Elo <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>.\nFurther, Ferdinand Mosca wrote multiple analysing tools, as well as <a href=\"/Games#ChessVariants\" title=\"Games\">chess variant</a> playing engines <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>, such as the <a href=\"/index.php?title=Spartan_Chess&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Spartan Chess (page does not exist)\">Spartan Chess</a> playing <a href=\"/index.php?title=Sangga&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Sangga (page does not exist)\">Sangga</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>, \nthe <a href=\"/index.php?title=Capablanca_Chess&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Capablanca Chess (page does not exist)\">Capablanca Chess</a> and <a href=\"/index.php?title=Gothic_Chess&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Gothic Chess (page does not exist)\">Gothic Chess</a> playing <a href=\"/index.php?title=Bihasa&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Bihasa (page does not exist)\">Bihasa</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>, \nthe <a href=\"/Shogi\" title=\"Shogi\">Shogi</a> engine <a href=\"/index.php?title=Siyam&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Siyam (page does not exist)\">Siyam</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>, \nand the mini Shogi engine <a href=\"/index.php?title=Lima&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Lima (page does not exist)\">Lima</a> which played a strong UEC Cup in 2015 <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p><p><span id=\"ChessGameAnalyzer\"></span>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Chess_Game_Analyzer\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Chess Game Analyzer</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Chess_Artist\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Chess Artist</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#aiBloodshed\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">aiBloodshed</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#2015_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2015 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#2020_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2020 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Chess_Game_Analyzer\">Chess Game Analyzer</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ferdinand_Mosca&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Chess Game Analyzer\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>In Fall 2015, Ferdinand Mosca introduced his <i>Chess Game Analyzer</i>, a <a href=\"/CLI\" title=\"CLI\">command line</a> <a href=\"/Utilities#PGN\" title=\"Utilities\">PGN tool</a>, working on <a href=\"/Portable_Game_Notation\" title=\"Portable Game Notation\">pgn files</a> as input and output, with scores, variations and annotations added as pgn comments after analyzing the games with an engine. The <i>Chess Game Analyzer</i> is written in <a href=\"/Python\" title=\"Python\">Python</a> using the <a href=\"/Python-chess\" title=\"Python-chess\">python-chess</a>  library to parse <a href=\"/Moves\" title=\"Moves\">moves</a> and <a href=\"/Chess_Position\" title=\"Chess Position\">positions</a> of the pgn file <sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>. In December 2016, Ferdinand Mosca announced the <i>Chess Game Analyzer</i> <a href=\"/GUI\" title=\"GUI\">GUI</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>.\n<span id=\"ChessArtist\"></span>\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Chess_Artist\">Chess Artist</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ferdinand_Mosca&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Chess Artist\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>Apparently the successor of the <i>Chess Game Analyzer</i> is <b>Chess Artist</b>, released in October 2016 under the  <a href=\"/Free_Software_Foundation#GPL\" title=\"Free Software Foundation\">GPLv3</a>  <sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>, a <a href=\"/Python\" title=\"Python\">Python</a> script that can annotate <a href=\"/Chess_Game\" title=\"Chess Game\">chess games</a> in <a href=\"/Portable_Game_Notation\" title=\"Portable Game Notation\">pgn file</a> with <a href=\"/Evaluation\" title=\"Evaluation\">static evaluation</a> or <a href=\"/Search\" title=\"Search\">search</a> <a href=\"/Score\" title=\"Score\">score</a> of an engine, can annotate games with <a href=\"/index.php?title=Cerebellum&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Cerebellum (page does not exist)\">Cerebellum</a> <a href=\"/Opening_Book\" title=\"Opening Book\">book moves</a> using the <a href=\"/Brainfish\" title=\"Brainfish\">Brainfish</a> engine with its Cerebellum_Light.bin book file, can annotate an <a href=\"/Extended_Position_Description\" title=\"Extended Position Description\">epd file</a> with <b>acd</b>, <b>acs</b>, <b>bm</b>, and <b>ce</b> <a href=\"/Extended_Position_Description#mnemonics\" title=\"Extended Position Description\">opcode mnemonics</a> and can <a href=\"/Engine_Testing\" title=\"Engine Testing\">test engines</a> with epd <a href=\"/Test-Positions\" title=\"Test-Positions\">test suites</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>. \n<span id=\"aiBloodshed\"></span>\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"aiBloodshed\">aiBloodshed</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ferdinand_Mosca&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: aiBloodshed\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><a href=\"/AiBloodshed\" title=\"AiBloodshed\">aiBloodshed</a> is a chess game <a href=\"/Web_Broadcast\" title=\"Web Broadcast\">web broadcaster</a> composed by Ferdinand Mosca, released in July 2017 <sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ferdinand_Mosca&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ferdinand_Mosca&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=39647&amp;start=2\">Re: Ideas from other engines ok?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 08, 2011</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=41034\">Spartan chess</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 09, 2011</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=41138\">Option questions on cutechess-cli</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 19, 2011&#160;» <a href=\"/Cutechess-cli\" title=\"Cutechess-cli\">Cutechess-cli</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=42106\">Bihasa v3.0 is released</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 19, 2011</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=41450\">Deuterium update and other engines</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 14, 2011</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=42720\">Clarification of uci option UCI_AnalyseMode</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 03, 2012&#160;» <a href=\"/UCI\" title=\"UCI\">UCI</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=43291\">New chess variants</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 03, 2012&#160;» <a href=\"/Games#ChessVariants\" title=\"Games\">Chess Variants</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2015_...\">2015 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ferdinand_Mosca&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: 2015 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=56028\">Game of the Generals</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 17, 2015</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=56435\">STS 1-15 epd and analysis tool</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 20, 2015&#160;» <a href=\"/Strategic_Test_Suite\" title=\"Strategic Test Suite\">Strategic Test Suite</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=56653\">STS test suite and engine analysis interface</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, June 11, 2015</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=57770\">Chess Game Analyzer</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 27, 2015&#160;» <a href=\"#ChessGameAnalyzer\">Chess Game Analyzer</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=58215\">Lima a mini shogi engine</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 10, 2015</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=58295\">Mandirigma a musketeer chess variant</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 19, 2015</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=58359&amp;start=2\">Re: Static evaluation test posistions</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 26, 2015&#160;» <a href=\"/Engine_Testing\" title=\"Engine Testing\">Engine Testing</a>, <a href=\"/Python\" title=\"Python\">Python</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=58379\">Sigla, seirawan chess variant engine</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 26, 2015</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=58381\">Siyam, a shogi 9x9 engine</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, November 26, 2015</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=58482\">Winboard 4.8.0b and Amazon chess variant</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 05, 2015&#160;» <a href=\"/WinBoard\" title=\"WinBoard\">WinBoard</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=58518\">Matibay an amazon chess variant engine</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 08, 2015</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=58533\">Masipag, a nightrider chess variant engine</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 09, 2015</li></ul>\n<p><b>2016</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=61723\">Chess Artist</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, October 15, 2016&#160;» <a href=\"#ChessArtist\">Chess Artist</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=62500\">Chess Game Analyzer GUI</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 16, 2016&#160;» <a href=\"#ChessGameAnalyzer\">Chess Game Analyzer</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=62615\">Bihasa 4.3.3</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 27, 2016</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=62624\">CDrill 1800</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 27, 2016</li></ul>\n<p><b>2017</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=64189&amp;start=42\">Re: Texel tuning method question</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 20, 2017&#160;» <a href=\"/Python\" title=\"Python\">Python</a>, <a href=\"/Texel%27s_Tuning_Method\" title=\"Texel&#39;s Tuning Method\">Texel's Tuning Method</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=64741\">aiBloodshed live broadcaster released</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 27, 2017&#160;» <a href=\"/AiBloodshed\" title=\"AiBloodshed\">aiBloodshed</a></li></ul>\n<p><b>2018</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=66853\">Chess Tools</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 17, 2018</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=67434\">NUCLEUS</a> by <a href=\"/Ed_Schroder\" title=\"Ed Schroder\">Ed Schroder</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 13, 2018</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=67578\">Deuterium 2018 released</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 27, 2018</li></ul>\n<p><b>2019</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=69721\">Deuterium v2019.1 released</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 25, 2019</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=70151\">EARS (Engine Analysis Reliability Score)</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 09, 2019</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=70339\">Yet another game analysis method</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 28, 2019</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=70385\">Tragic comedy in pondering</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 02, 2019&#160;» <a href=\"/Pondering\" title=\"Pondering\">Pondering</a>, <a href=\"/Stalemate\" title=\"Stalemate\">Stalemate</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=70390\">How to measure overall similarity</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 02, 2019</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=70426\">Test sets results on opening, tactical, ending</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 06, 2019&#160;» <a href=\"/Test-Positions\" title=\"Test-Positions\">Test-Positions</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=70472\">Positional and Tactical</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 11, 2019&#160;» <a href=\"/Strategy\" title=\"Strategy\">Strategy</a>, <a href=\"/Tactics\" title=\"Tactics\">Tactics</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=71875\">Deuterium released</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 21, 2019</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=71876\">Siyam released</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 21, 2019</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2020_...\">2020 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Ferdinand_Mosca&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: 2020 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=75104\">Yet another parameter tuner using optuna framework</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 14, 2020&#160;» <a href=\"/Automated_Tuning\" title=\"Automated Tuning\">Automated Tuning</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=76198\">Evaluation of moves from World Championship Games</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, December 31, 2020&#160;» <a href=\"/Playing_Strength\" title=\"Playing Strength\">Playing Strength</a></li></ul>\n<p><b>2021</b>\n</p>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=76380\">Texel tuning variant</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Ferdinand Mosca</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 21, 2021&#160;» <a href=\"/Texel%27s_Tuning_Method\" title=\"Texel&#39;s Tuning Method\">Texel's Tuning Method</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=76446\">So what do we miss in the traditional evaluation?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selfl